comments.content:
I think both are [Frankfurter Bold](http://web.archive.org/web/20081202063801/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/efscangraphic/frankfurter-sb/bold/).

[VAG Rounded, or VAG Rundschrift](http://web.archive.org/web/20081202063801/http:/www.myfonts.com/search?search%5Btext%5D=VAG) is similar.

fyi - village just released a new font by Jeremy Mickel that is something new on the rounded front:

[https://www.vllg.com/Incubator/Router/mudTyper+Weights/](http://web.archive.org/web/20081202063801/https:/www.vllg.com/Incubator/Router/mudTyper+Weights/ "https://www.vllg.com/Incubator/Router/mudTyper+Weights/")
Also similar, but not quite as bold - [Gotham Rounded](http://web.archive.org/web/20081202063801/http:/www.typography.com/fonts/font_overview.php?productLineID=100030).
Take a look at [Corpulent](http://web.archive.org/web/20081202063801/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/suitcase/corpulent/) by Suitcase Type Foundry.
